                                <break/> Governance</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td align="left" colspan="1" rowspan="1" valign="top">The EU and Member States should ensure the systematic application of penalization and/or reward systems
                                <break/> at local level, to encourage citizens to properly sort biowaste. Actually, local governments, 
                                <italic toggle="yes">i.e.</italic>: the owners and
                                <break/> responsible of generated waste, are often hesitant to promulgate ordinances that imply unpopular measures like 
                                <break/>economic penalization of citizens uncomplying with proper separate collection, because these measures are not 
